Principle

Temporal Leverage Principle

A finite system can generate extremely large effective experience by reusing structure while varying traversal.

Compression Principle

Do not store every pass independently. Store base state + delta + outcome class.

Anti-Paradox Principle

The engine does not “go back in time.” It revisits prior paths by reweighting, replaying, and recombining transition chains.

Metric Principle

Value is measured not by runtime length alone, but by:

	•	novelty
	•	coverage
	•	strategic yield
	•	invariance retention

