Core Metrics

1. Traversal Length

Raw path duration or number of state transitions.

Useful, but insufficient alone.

⸻

2. Novelty Ratio

Novelty Ratio = unique meaningful transitions / total transitions

Measures whether the loop is actually producing fresh value.

⸻

3. Redundancy Load

Redundancy Load = repeated low-yield transitions / total transitions

High redundancy means the engine is spinning wheels.

⸻

4. Yield Density

Yield Density = lessons extracted / unit traversal

Measures how much useful output is generated per loop segment.

⸻

5. Branch Coverage

Branch Coverage = explored branches / reachable branches

Useful for scenario planning and adversarial simulation.

⸻

6. Invariant Retention

Measures whether core truths remain stable under repeated traversal.

Examples:
	•	ethics retained
	•	constraints honored
	•	realism preserved
	•	no hallucinated gains

⸻

7. Effective Temporal Depth

Composite metric.

ETD = traversal length * novelty * yield * coherence

This is the preferred top-level metric.

