Failure Modes

1. False Novelty

The engine treats cosmetic variation as meaningful difference.

Guard: Mirror semantic equivalence checks

2. Infinite Spin

The engine optimizes path length instead of yield.

Guard: yield-weighted scoring

3. Reality Drift

Synthetic loop behavior diverges from plausible system dynamics.

Guard: The Well grounding / realism priors

4. Overcompression

Important branch differences are collapsed too early.

Guard: uncertainty retention + shadow branch storage

5. Narrative Seduction

Interesting loops are preferred over accurate loops.

Guard: Checksum + realism score + explicit confidence tags

